org.gradoop.flink.model.api.functions

Interface KeyFunction<E,K>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the object from which the grouping key is extracted.
    K - The type of the extracted key.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    KeyFunctionWithDefaultValue<E,K>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CompositeKeyFunction, CompositeKeyFunctionWithDefaultValues, ConstantKeyFunction, LabelKeyFunction, LabelSpecificKeyFunction, PropertyKeyFunction

    public interface KeyFunction<E,K>
extends Serializable
    A function extracting a key from an element. This key may be used as a grouping key. The key will be an object of a certain type, depending on this function.

      • addKeyToElement

        default void addKeyToElement(E element,
                             Object key)
        Store a key on an element.

        This is used to store the grouping key on the super element after grouping.

        The default implementation of this function does not change the element.

        Parameters:
        element - The element where the key should be stored.
        key - The key to store on the element. The type of the key is expected to be the same as the type of keys extracted by this key function.
